# LF enforcement for build-CRITICAL files. The GNU toolchain (cc1, maspsx,
# GNU as/ld) and bash break on CRLF (\r). See AGENTS.md "File-edit conventions".
#
# SCOPED deliberately: only patterns confirmed to be LF already, so adding this
# file does NOT renormalize existing CRLF/vendored files (e.g. tools/maspsx/**
# DOS .S files, some generated asm/*.s). The LIVE net for new CRLF is the
# post-write check in tools/hooks/tooling_error_guard.py. To extend coverage to
# another path, add it here ONLY after confirming `git status` stays clean.
# See docs/TOOLING_ERROR_GUARD.md.

# C source / headers (decompiled code)
*.c                  text eol=lf
*.h                  text eol=lf

# Permuter workspace .c files (gitignored, but if ever added or staged the
# eol=lf attribute will apply). Native Edit tool can introduce CRLF on these
# (incident 2026-05-30); for editing prefer Write tool or WSL sed/perl.
permuter/**/*.c      text eol=lf
permuter/**/*.h      text eol=lf
permuter/**/base.c.orig text eol=lf

# Build driver
Makefile             text eol=lf
*.ld                 text eol=lf

# LF-critical pipeline config (per AGENTS.md)
regfix.txt           text eol=lf
asmfix.txt           text eol=lf
regfix_stage2.txt    text eol=lf
named_syms.txt       text eol=lf
expand_lb_funcs.txt  text eol=lf
symbol_addrs.txt     text eol=lf
inline_asm_canonical.txt text eol=lf
sdata*.txt           text eol=lf
